meanings.definition: The act of breathing excessively or too deeply.
meanings.sent1: After running for a long time, his overbreathings were noticeable.
meanings.sent2: She felt better after her overbreathings calmed down.
meanings.sent3: His overbreathings during the yoga class made everyone giggle.
meanings.sent4: The overbreathings of the exhausted hiker echoed through the valley.
meanings.sent5: The doctor warned him about the dangers of overbreathings during panic attacks.
